text.tspan: Pitta is a passionate determined and methodical soul.
With penetrating intellect, Pitta can make an excellent leader
and steward of dynamic innovation. Usually of medium weight
and build, Pitta skin tends to be sensitive or combination with
congestion in the t-zone. Common skin imbalances are: redness,
inflammation, breakouts, acne, rosacea, and eczema.
According to Ayurveda, a number of factors determine skin
health and youthfulness, and these include proper moisture
balance, effective functioning of the metabolic mechanisms
that coordinate the various chemical and hormonal reactions
of the skin, and efficient circulation of blood, lymph, and
nutrients to the different layers of the skin. The health of
the following three types of body tissue are especially reflected
in the skin: nutritional fluid/plasma, blood, and muscle.
To be effective, a skincare regimen has to provide support
Skincare products should be both cooling and nurturing,
with resistance or protection from the sun. Avoid harsh synthetic
cosmetics as they tend to irritate sensitive Pitta skin types.
Less is more for Pitta, simple all-natural formulations work best.
Amalaki Capsules; Pinda Oil (cracked feet/skin); Winsoria Oil (ezcema, psoriasis,
flaky skin); Kesini Hair Oil; Arimedadi Oil (mouth rinse)
Aim for astringent, bitter, and sweet tastes to balance Pitta. Avoid hot, spicy foods,
oily foods. Watch for unripened sour fruits, yogurt, tomatoes and vinegar.
- Cautious with not over indulging in meat particularly red meats
- Cooling spices like fennel, licorice, cardamom, and mint
- Moderate consumption of alchohol, coffee, orange/tomato/pineapple/lemon juices
- Meditation is super beneficial, as Pitta types need to learn to surrender and
not try to strive for control over everyday life. Use ram mantra to open heart
energy to allow more compassion/sweetness and cooling of heating
- Ideal environment is cool and dry
